    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Simple, wooden slat-back chairs with a seat usually of woven material, originating in Chiavari, Italy. Mass-produced chairs have been based on this design, including Gio Ponti's 'Superleggera' chair of the 1950s.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000030811/Oxford Companion to the Decorative Arts (1975)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000003271/Aslin, 19th Century English Furniture (1962)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>風格簡潔的木製條板椅，椅墊通常採用編織材料，起源於義大利齊亞瓦里(Chiavari)。此一設計孕育出許多大量生產的不同風格椅子，例如喬•龐帝(Gio Ponti)於西元1950年代所設計的超輕椅(Superleggera chair)。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
